    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy)</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[7 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[10 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the<strong> drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your<strong> pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> between the<strong> </strong>pizza<strong> </strong>base[s]<strong> </strong>and spread it evenly all over them with the back of a spoon</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the<strong> pizza[s]</strong> with the <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>and <strong>softened pepper</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base is crispy</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pizza[s] are in the oven, combine your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>balsamic</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once cooked, remove the pizza[s] from the oven and break your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> up all over them \u2013 this is your <strong>goats' cheese & pepper pizza</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-pepper-pizza/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>goats' cheese & pepper pizza</strong> with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>salad</strong> with the <strong>balsamic dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
